race.comment: VICTORY FLAME (8) got a well-deserved win over this track and trip last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that victory. Should get a gun run in transit from gate three and can make it back-to-back wins without surprising. MAZIS (4) returned in fine fashion with a solid win here and gun hoop Maloney sticks in the saddle. Ready for the step-up in trip now. Import BRAVE CALL (9) has been right there in all three runs since landing on our shores and will strip fitter second-up from the break. Top-three commodity. The well-related SECOND SUN (6) (half to G3 winner and G2 placed Beadman) has placed over this course and distance and looks a must for the multiples. CAVALRY MAN (1) also hails from a handy family (half to G2 winner Positive Peace) and may earn some minor money with the 3kg claim.
